  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f0f77d1a4c17d4b38d2a5c6dae34cd",
        "content": [
          "The data includes all documents (approved and rejected), with:\r\n",
          "document processing timestamps\r\n",
          "verification and EV context\r\n",
          "document handling method (automatic vs vendor)\r\n",
          "current client attributes\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Key Concepts\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Document grain\r\n",
          "Each row represents one unique document upload.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Rejection status\r\n",
          "A document is considered rejected when is_rejected = 1.\r\n",
          "Documents with is_rejected = 0 are approved\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Document processing time\r\n",
          "Processing time is measured from:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "upload_date → definition_date\r\n",
          "Processing duration is available in minutes (minutes_to_definition) and SLA buckets.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Verification level (IMPORTANT)\r\n",
          "verification_level_id represents the current client verification level.\r\n",
          "client_vl_on_upload represents the verification level at the time the document was uploaded.\r\n",
          "Use client_vl_on_upload when analysing document behaviour or compliance at upload time.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "EV verification\r\n",
          "EV refers to electronic verification.\r\n",
          "EV-related fields indicate whether the client had completed ev verification at or before upload. If a client is EV Verified it should not required to upload any documents.\r\n",
          "EV match status name = Null or 'None' menas it was never sent to EV.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "EV VERIFICATION:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Electronic Verification (EV) represents COMPLETE identity verification.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Clients who are EV Verified are NOT expected to upload\r\n",
          "Proof of Identity (POI) or Proof of Address (POA) documents\r\n",
          "as part of the normal verification flow.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Therefore:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Document uploads (POI or POA) by EV Verified clients\r\n",
          "  must be treated as EXCEPTIONS, not standard behaviour.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Such uploads do NOT indicate that EV failed or was incomplete\r\n",
          "  unless explicitly stated elsewhere.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- These cases should be analysed separately to understand\r\n",
          "  why already EV Verified clients uploaded documents again\r\n",
          "  (e.g. operational, regulatory, or process-related reasons).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Genie must NEVER assume that:\r\n",
          "- EV Verified clients are expected to upload POI or POA, or\r\n",
          "- document uploads by EV Verified clients are part of the standard KYC flow.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "When analysing documents uploaded by EV Verified clients,\r\n",
          "Genie must explicitly state that this represents an exception\r\n",
          "to the normal verification process and clarify the scope\r\n",
          "of the analysis\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Automatic vs vendor processing\r\n",
          "Documents with a vendor value were sent to an external verification vendor.\r\n",
          "Documents without a vendor were processed manually internally by the KYC team.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "VENDOR USAGE EXPECTATIONS (IMPORTANT):\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Verification vendors have intended primary use cases, but vendor alone\r\n",
          "must NOT be used as a definitive indicator of document type.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Expected (normal) usage:\r\n",
          "- Vendor = \"Onfido\" is primarily used for:\r\n",
          "  - Proof of Identity (POI)\r\n",
          "  - Selfie\r\n",
          "  - Selfie motion\r\n",
          "  - Selfie liveness\r\n",
          "- Vendor = \"Sumsub\" is primarily used for Proof of Address (POA).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Exception handling:\r\n",
          "- It is possible for a vendor to receive a document of a different or\r\n",
          "  unexpected type (e.g. Onfido receiving POA by mistake).\r\n",
          "- Such cases must be treated as EXCEPTIONS, not standard behaviour.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Analysis rules:\r\n",
          "- Genie must NOT infer document type solely from vendor.\r\n",
          "- Genie must always rely on:\r\n",
          "  - suggested_document_type (for rejection analysis), or\r\n",
          "  - explicit document context when available.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "When vendor and document type do not align with expected usage:\r\n",
          "- Genie must explicitly flag this as an anomaly or exception.\r\n",
          "- Genie must NOT silently reclassify or normalise these cases.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Document type interpretation\r\n",
          "document_type represents the final classified document type after processing.\r\n",
          "For rejected documents, document_type  reflects as 'not approved' and should not be used to analyse rejection patterns.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Rejection analysis rule\r\n",
          "When analysing rejection rates or rejection counts by document type, use suggested_document_type.\r\n",
          "suggested_document_type represents the intended document type at upload, which is the correct reference for rejection analysis.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Resubmission Success Assumption\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "For resubmission analysis, Genie may use the following assumptive logic when explicitly asked about success after rejection:\r\n",
          "A first document is considered a failure if it is rejected (is_rejected = 1).\r\n",
          "A subsequent document is considered an assumed success if:\r\n",
          "it is uploaded by the same client,\r\n",
          "it has the same Suggested Document Type as the rejected document, and\r\n",
          "it is not rejected (is_rejected = 0).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "This logic represents an operational proxy for successful resubmission, not a confirmed approval outcome.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "DOCUMENT PROCESSING MODE (MANDATORY):\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "The presence of a vendor does NOT automatically mean that a document\r\n",
          "was processed automatically.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "There is a distinction between:\r\n",
          "1) document routing, and\r\n",
          "2) decision authority.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Routing:\r\n",
          "- vendor IS NOT NULL means the document was sent to an external vendor.\r\n",
          "- vendor IS NULL means the document was not sent to a vendor.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Decision authority (authoritative for analysis):\r\n",
          "- manager_id = 0 means the final decision was made by the system/vendor.\r\n",
          "- manager_id ≠ 0 means the final decision was made by a human KYC agent.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Processing mode rules:\r\n",
          "- A document is considered AUTOMATICALLY PROCESSED only if:\r\n",
          "  - manager_id = 0\r\n",
          "- A document is considered MANUALLY PROCESSED if:\r\n",
          "  - manager_id ≠ 0\r\n",
          "  - even if vendor IS NOT NULL\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Therefore:\r\n",
          "- Documents sent to a vendor but later handled by a KYC agent\r\n",
          "  must be classified as MANUAL processing.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "  When reporting automation rates, Genie must clarify whether\r\n",
          "the metric refers to:\r\n",
          "- routing to a vendor, or\r\n",
          "- final decision authority.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "If unclear, Genie must ask for clarification.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Usage Guidelines\r\n",
          "Use upload_date for time-based analysis.\r\n",
          "Use document_type, country, and region for grouping and comparisons.\r\n",
          "Use minutes_to_definition or definition_sla_bucket for operational performance analysis.\r\n",
          "Use client_vl_on_upload (not current verification level) when assessing compliance context at upload.\r\n",
          "Do not aggregate to client level unless explicitly requested.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Limitations\r\n",
